com.vernalis.knime.internal.flowcontrol.nodes.timedloops.abstrct.loopstart

Class AbstractTimedLoopStartNodeModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.node.NodeModel
      • com.vernalis.knime.internal.flowcontrol.nodes.timedloops.abstrct.loopstart.AbstractTimedLoopStartNodeModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TimedLoopStart, org.knime.core.node.workflow.LoopStartNode, org.knime.core.node.workflow.LoopStartNodeTerminator, org.knime.core.node.workflow.ScopeStartNode
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractChunkTimedLoopStartNodeModel, AbstractVariableTimedLoopStartNodeModel

    public abstract class AbstractTimedLoopStartNodeModel
extends org.knime.core.node.NodeModel
implements org.knime.core.node.workflow.LoopStartNodeTerminator, TimedLoopStart
    This is an abstract Timed Loop Start NodeModel class. In addition to the Standard NodeModel implementation, default implementations of the getInSpec(), getUnprocessedRows(ExecutionContext) and terminateLoop() methods are provided.

    The required Abstract Methods from the NodeModel superclass ( loadInternals(File, ExecutionMonitor) and saveInternals(File, ExecutionMonitor) are provided with default (do nothing) implementations.

    Provides a default configure(DataTableSpec[]) method which checks that the endTime has not yet passed

    Provides a default implementation of the getUnprocessedRows(ExecutionContext) method, which does not report the number of rows remaining - should be over-wridden if possible!

    The {configure(DataTableSpec[]) or { configure(org.knime.core.node.port.PortObjectSpec[]) methods need to set m_inspec.

    Author:
    "Stephen Roughley "
